author=";s:4:"slug";s:31:"28:how-do-i-install-ciws-server";s:7:"catslug";s:10:"31:general";}i:2;O:8:"stdClass":32:{s:2:"id";s:2:"25";s:5:"title";s:46:"What are the requirements to run a Ciws server";s:5:"alias";s:41:"what-are-the-requirements-to-run-ciws-052";s:11:"title_alias";s:0:"";s:9:"introtext";s:789:"<div class="level2">  <p> In fact it depends of the contents of your Ciws server. </p>  <p> In every case you need a Intel-compatible CPU (i486 or later), bootable CD-ROM drive or Usb bootable motherboard. </p>  <p> To boot the demo Live CD, you need at least 1Gb RAM. </p>  <p> To boot the demo Live DVD, you need at least 1,5Gb RAM. </p>  <p> To boot demo USB, you need at least 1Gb RAM. </p>  <p>  But if you make your custom Cooperation-iws and if you only choose small applications (like blog <acronym title="Content Management System">CMS</acronym>), you might boot USB with 256Mb RAM.</p>  </div>  <h2><a name="where_can_i_get_cooperation-iws_cd_dvd" title="where_can_i_get_cooperation-iws_cd_dvd"></a></h2><a href="http://forum.joomla.org" title="The Joomla! Community Forums"></a>";s:8:"fulltext";s:0:"";s:5:"state";s:1:"1";s:9:"sectionid";s:1:"3";s:4:"mask";s:1:"0";s:5:"catid";s:2:"31";s:7:"created";s:19:"2006-10-11 00:42:31";s:10:"created_by";s:2:"62";s:16:"created_by_alias";s:0:"";s:8:"modified";s:19:"2008-10-20 12:43:08";s:11:"modified_by";s:2:"62";s:11:"checked_out";s:1:"0";s:16:"checked_out_time";s:19:"0000-00-00 00:00:00";s:10:"publish_up";s:19:"2006-10-10 06:00:00";s:12:"publish_down";s:19:"0000-00-00 00:00:00";s:6:"images";s:0:"";s:4:"urls";s:0:"";s:7:"attribs";s:231:"show_title=
